## Spectral resolution

1) Low resolution

0.3-0.7 micron @ 0.02 micron, 20 bands
0.7-4.0 micron @ 0.1  micron, 33 bands
total 53 bands

2) High resolution

0.3-4.0 micron @ 0.005 micron, 740 bands


## Gases

Parameters of Rayleigh scattering & gaseous absorption are saved in "gas_??" files. Two versions with different spectral resolution are provided.

Single band model is used now instead of the 3-term k-distribution.


## Solar incident irradiance

The database is now given for the spectral range, 0.2 to 4.0 micron, with interval of 0.001 micron. The data were taken from Lowtran-7 (using 4-point polynomial interpolation).


## Mie optical parameters: Aerosols and clouds

Two versions with different spectral resolution are provided. Parameters of aerosols with hygroscopicity are provided for discrete relative humidity values:

RH = 0, 50, 70, 80, 90, 95, 98, 99%.

